		<technology>
			<technologicalApplicability xml:lang="en">The cement clinker described by this data set is produced using a new dry process with a daily production capacity of more than 4000 tonnes. It incorporates 16% copper tailings as part of its composition. This type of clinker is a key component in the production of Portland cement, which is a fundamental material in the construction industry, used for creating concrete, mortar, stucco, and grout for building, infrastructure, and general construction purposes.</technologicalApplicability>
			<technologicalApplicability xml:lang="zh">本数据集描述的水泥熟料采用日产能超过4000吨的新型干法生产，并且在其组成中加入了16%的铜尾矿。该类型的熟料是波特兰水泥生产的关键成分，波特兰水泥是建筑行业的基础材料，用于建筑、基础设施以及一般建设用途的混凝土、砂浆、灰泥和灌浆材料。</technologicalApplicability>
			<referenceToTechnologyFlowDiagrammOrPicture type="source data set" refObjectId="83c2f7f9-63d5-75a7-4567-6050f14137a3" uri="../sources/83c2f7f9-63d5-75a7-4567-6050f14137a3.xml">
				<common:shortDescription xml:lang="en">SSvFbtoANoZ8LXxVfYEcsH8pn9e.png</common:shortDescription>
			</referenceToTechnologyFlowDiagrammOrPicture>
		</technology>
